      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "VEINS WITHIN ROCK (2) won here Maiden by 10L at Launceston over a mile and then he stepped up to this trip here and won comfortably. Has the top hoop on again and tumbles in weight at this level. Has a low gate and can go on with the job. HAPPY CLAN (1) was quickly back on track beaten just 1.6L over a mile at Launceston. Has won this course and distance and rates to go close. FLORENCE GLASS (4) won a 64 here over 2000m as an equal favourite. Maps for a soft run and is a chance to go on. IFFYCOULD (3) was the other equal favourite in that contest beaten 1.9L.  Ran home well and is also in the mix. RESERVOIR DOG (7) sits down in the weights and would be a hope, forgiving the latest against the above pair.",
